UID:10003857-1774083600-1774090800@www.unioncong.org
SUMMARY:Women's Breakfast (Lambert Castle)
DESCRIPTION:Join us to visit the historic Lambert Castle  \nThe Women of Union will be taking a tour of the amazing\, newly restored Lambert Castle located at 3 Valley Road in Paterson. \nThe tour will take place on Saturday\, March 21 at 10:00 am at the Lambert Castle. \n“The Castle\,” a well-known landmark in Northern New Jersey\, is located on Garret Mountain overlooking the City of Paterson. Once a private residence\, the building is fashioned after an English castle.  Catholina Lambert\, an English immigrant who made his fortune in the silk industry\, built the Castle in 1892-93.   He named it “Belle Vista.” \nWe will travel to a diner for lunch after the tour. \nWe will meet at church at 9:15 am to carpool to the castle. (This will take place of the monthly Women’s Breakfast.) \nPlease email Karen Ermler at karen.ermler@gmail.com so we can let the tour guide know how many will be attending. \nThis is an awesome historic opportunity!
URL:https://www.unioncong.org/event/womens-breakfast-assembly-room-4-6/
LOCATION:Assembly Room
CATEGORIES:All Church Events,All Events,Featured Events,Small Groups
ORGANIZER;CN="Union Congregational Event":MAILTO:contact@unioncong.org
END:VEVENT
